      "note_no": "63",
      "note": "I.e., what men conceive of as \"time\" has no meaning with regard to God, because He is timeless, without beginning and without end, so that \"in rejation to Him, one day and a thousand years are alike\" (Razi). Cf. 70:4, where in the same sense, a \"day\" is said to be equal to \"fifty thousand years\", or the well-authenticated saying of the Prophet, \"God says, 'I am Time Absolute (ad-dahr)'\"."
